03/20/85 auto_start_delay

Syntax as a command:  auto_start_delay {N}


Function:  displays or sets the length of time the driver will wait to
issue the start command automatically after receiving a quit signal.
An automatic start is cancelled if command input is received.


Arguments:
N
   is the desired delay time in seconds.  N must be at least 30
   seconds.  The default delay time is 60 seconds.  When no argument is
   given, the current delay time is displayed.
